aphQL which I found very amazing to use. ","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":1751},"end":{"line":25,"column":332,"offset":2082},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":1751},"end":{"line":25,"column":332,"offset":2082},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"From a CSS standpoint, I wanted to learn how to use Styled Components so I decided to use this particular CSS framework. ","position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1,"offset":2084},"end":{"line":27,"column":122,"offset":2205},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1,"offset":2084},"end":{"line":27,"column":122,"offset":2205},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next, I needed to figure out how to host content on my site. The simplest thing I could've done was to use was to create the posts on my repo but I wanted to have the experience of using a headless CMS and found the Contentful to be very intuitive (bonus points to Gatsby for also having great documentation on implementing Contentful). So, I'm currently writing this post on Contentful. ","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1,"offset":2207},"end":{"line":29,"column":389,"offset":2595},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1,"offset":2207},"end":{"line":29,"column":389,"offset":2595},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, I needed to find somewhere to host this thing. After experience with zeit/now and Firebase, I decided to continue on the serverless trend and use another service called Netlify. ","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1,"offset":2597},"end":{"line":31,"column":188,"offset":2784},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1,"offset":2597},"end":{"line":31,"column":188,"offset":2784},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":1,"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The result","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":3,"offset":2788},"end":{"line":33,"colu